1�Hah hah! I found you! Come on out!
1�Ugly!? That's what you'll be once I'm done pounding your faces in! Now get outta here if you know what's good for you!
1�Punish you!? Go home now, and I might just not kill you!
1�How many times have I told you that you're too young to go off adventuring on your own!?

1�Yeah, there might be some big, hungry tiger with a craving for juicy Tarutaru hiding behind that tree right over there! Until I've checked this place out first, I want you three back in your rooms!
1�Hell right, I'm not worried. Why should I worry about what happens to those traitors? I don't care who they are--if they're in my way, they're not on my side!
y!�Ugly!? Why, you little creeps! I'll show you ugly!
1�What the--?Where did they go!?
1�Oooh, when I get my hands on those three...
1�Yes, off with you children! Unless you want to see Prishe become truly upset.
1�Exactly! Do you not remember the last time you went out alone? It took over a month for your wounds to heal!
1�And these are not the fields outside the safehold. Who knows what horrors lie in the deeper parts of this strange place...
1�Prishe...You are not worried about them at all, are you? You just...
1�We'll go home, but only if Prishe promises not to punish us!
e!�You're so ugl
1�She's found us, and boy, does she look ugly!
n!�You're so terribl
1�She's found us, and boy, does she look mad!
1�You're so mea
1�Oh my Gob! You're one of those adventurerurers, aren't ya?You got nothin' on me, ?[man./lady.] I was just mindin' my own businesesess, lookin' for junk an' stuff.
1�Hey, watch out. You don't wanna fight me. I'll turn you into meat jerky!Wait, how about you and me be friends instead? Sound good?
1�I travel all over the world and hear lots of differererent stories. I even hear your stories. I can tell you one, if you want.
1�Do you want to hear a story?No, thank you.Let's hear one.

1�What story would you like to be told?On second thought, maybe later.Ancient Vows.The Search for Goldmane(pt.1).The Search for Goldmane(pt.2).Confessions of a Bellmaker(pt.1).Confessions of a Bellmaker(pt.2).Confessions of a Bellmaker(pt.3).
1�Oh...Well, if that's the case, I'm outta here.
1�Oh...Well, if that's the case, I'm outta here.
1�Oh...Well, if that's the case, I'm outta here.
1�Oh...Well, if that's the case, I'm outta here.
1�Oh...Well, if that's the case, I'm outta here.
1�Now, listen close...
1�Enter the displacement?Yes.No.
1�You open the trunk with the key!
1�It's the same as everywhere else.Everything in ruins...
1�No.I have to find Goldmane, no matter what.
1�I'm not leaving until I find some clues.
1�I see where this is going.
1�But I don't need your help.I have to be wary of people I don't know in this line of work.
1�I don't need that either.
1�Fine.If you find something around here that belonged to Goldmane, I'll take the package off your hands.
1�I don't think I'm being difficult.
1�Oooh!
1�I saw that!What did you find? Lemme see!Is it anything to do with Goldmane!?
1�A picture of three kids and...a letter.
1�Let's see here...This is from Naval Recruit Training Officer Vladinek, of the Bastokan navy.
1�That's it!Goldmane is under the protection of the Bastokan navy!
1�Since the navy is always at sea, no one can ever find him!
1�Right, it's off to Bastok.
1�All the villagers had to abandon their homes when the war began, kupopo.
1�And not so long ago the Wyrmking returned, causing all...this, kupopo.
1�I think we can safely assume there are no bounty hunters here.Let's get back to ground that's, well, on the ground, kupopo.
1�This is the territory of the Wyrmking.Even a moogle like me can't match the power of Bahamut.
1�Kupopo?
1�Look, Sanctia, it's the adventurer that was searching for you, kupopo!
1�Have you come to make sure she's okay again, kupopo?
1�I'm really sorry about this, kupopo.
1�We'll at least take the package you brought from Sanctia's dad, kupopo.
1�But, Sanctia!This poor adventurer has traveled across half the world to deliver this to you, kupopo!
1�Why are you being so difficult, kupopo!?
1�Just a...Hey, wait for me, kupopopopopo!
1�What about the package the adventurer brought, kupopo!?
1�<Sigh>Just look at what's happened here...
1�I thought I had finally found a nice, quiet place.
1�And then one day there's this terrible explosion and the whole peninsula is thrust up into the sky. Look at my bell--split right in two.
1�Hey, you.
1�You must understand what I'm talking about.There isn't really much a man like me can do.
1�Hello?You can see me, right?I can see you...
1�Hmph...I wonder why that is...
1�Anyway, that bell is the one reason I originally traveled here.The clear tone as it rang across the meadows...it had the power to make all other things seem like they didn't even matter.
1�Pain, suffering...even the passing of time melted away like mist on a summer morning when that bell sang her ethereal song...
1�I was content. My soul had finally found a place to spend eternity.
1�And that is why I cannot leave...but without the celestial ringing my heart yearns for, my soul remains restless.
1�You see...
1�With the bell in its current state, I'm lost. You must help me repair it.
1�I want to share its music with you--and the rest of the world.
1�Here, I have something that may assist you. It's a scroll with an intricately carved jade fastener.
1�I don't remember where I found it, but I feel that it is very important.
1�Let me read it for you, though it is quite old and tattered...
1�??...Bast......uild...smiths of......nd gold...???
1�I'm not sure what to make of this cryptic message.
1�But something tells me you already know where you must travel.Good luck. I shall be waiting here for your return.
1�Welcome back, traveler. I have been so looking forward to your return.
1�Were you able to find someone who can repair the bell?
1�It has seemed like an eternity since you first visited.
1�I was quite lonely while you were gone. I do not get many visitors around here, and since the bell was damaged, my mind has not been feeling too well.
1�Now, come, tell me quickly. What have you discovered?
1�What? Is that all?
1�I thought you, of all people, understood how I felt. I thought you understood what that bell means to me!
1�But I was wrong. And now I have nothing...
1�My reason for existence has begun to fade...
1�...and it is all your fault!
1�Begone, and never return!...Unless you yearn to witness the undying wrath of my battered soul!
1�Where... Where am I?
1�Who is that...? Why is he looking at me?
1�I... I don't know.
1�I heard the angels, and followed their song... And here I am.
1�I've done it... I've finally found the sound for which I was searching.
1�That is enough for today.
1�Ah!Wh-who are you!? How did you get in here?
1�I can't stop now... I must complete...the bell...
1�I must finish...for him...
1�I must listen... I must do what he says...
1�......Why won't he leave me alone...? Why...?
1�No. I must not think these thoughts. I must finish the bell...
1�I must...
1�I've got it! Why didn't I think of it before!?
1�If I take the bell there, he'll never bother me again, ever. Yes. If I take the bell there...
1�Finally, my work is done. And soon I will be free.No longer will this bell torment me, for I shall travel far away to a land its call cannot reach.
1�However, no matter where I run, I fear the memory of its spirit will haunt me...
1�...for all eternity...
